# Completion Review

- Feature: added the additive `fmo-pools/v1` publisher slice. FMO can now build
  publisher stages (`hermes-inventory`, `role-lifecycle`, `demand-forecast`,
  `compose`, `publish`, `usage-feedback`), compose pool specs from role policy
  plus demand forecasts without capacity/model-score reads, fail closed when a
  pool lacks `min_context_tokens`, publish one payload to `/api/fmo/pools` with
  payload-hash idempotency, and persist acknowledgements in
  `published_generations`. Coverage drift from existing dirty spec work was
  fixed by aligning stale markers and updating `tests/spec_coverage_pending.txt`.
  Code Simplifier review reused one stage-adapter set and added explicit fake
  client annotations. Verification: focused publisher/spec-coverage pytest,
  ruff on touched files, `git diff --check`, and OpenSpec strict validation.
- Deploy fix: daily probe now delegates live model health to OmniRoute's
  `/api/models/test-all` instead of the removed raw `/v1/chat/completions`
  probe helper. The probe stage uses the current live catalog preflight rows,
  skips final-path `-auto` aliases, groups eligible models by provider and
  connection, chunks `modelIds` at 100, sends `respectRateLimit=true` and
  `autoHideFailed=true`, persists each returned model-test entry as a separate
  endpoint probe, and fail-closes missing/rate-limited batch entries. After
  test-all runs, FMO immediately rereads `/api/providers` and `/v1/models`
  instead of parsing OmniRoute visibility internals; the existing live catalog
  scanner tombstones anything no longer active in the same daily run. The old
  raw probe endpoint helper and tests were removed rather than kept for
  compatibility. Verification: focused runtime/sweep/scoring/catalog/e2e tests,
  ruff on touched files,
  `git diff --check`, and OpenSpec strict validation.
- Deploy fix: FMO now treats OmniRoute active provider/model state as the
  source of truth before any decision stage. The composed runtime refreshes
  `GET /api/providers` and `GET /v1/models` before commands and scheduled
  pipelines read cached endpoint rows; disabled/absent providers and accounts
  are marked disabled, absent active models are tombstoned, and reappearing
  models clear `removed_at`. Old cache rows from a previous OmniRoute instance
  id are disabled too. Matching, quota research, access classification, probing,
  telemetry, role scoring, allocation, and provider sweep candidate reads now
  exclude disabled or tombstoned rows, and direct `apply` blocks old diffs whose
  desired endpoints are no longer active. This fixes the stale-cache failure
  where FMO could still test/allocate Nvidia rows after Nvidia was disabled in
  OmniRoute. Verification: focused catalog/sweep/runtime/apply tests, ruff on
  touched files, `git diff --check`, and OpenSpec strict validation.
- Feature: added explicit `sweep-provider-models` operator command for provider
  catalog probing. It walks stored endpoints for one provider with
  `--limit`, `--offset`, `--delay-seconds`, `--timeout-seconds`, `--dry-run`,
  `--force`, and `--json`, now calls OmniRoute's `/api/models/test` model-test
  route with stored provider/model/connection identity, records
  `endpoint_probes`, updates endpoint `probe_status`, and prints a per-model
  pass/fail/skip report. Live specs document that this command is the
  intentional full-provider sweep path, while the default `probe-models` stage
  remains seed-bounded for live safety. The first deployed sweep used an
  FMO-only raw chat probe; that was the wrong truth source for OmniRoute UI
  model availability. The corrected command records model-test evidence matching
  OmniRoute `/api/models/test` and live flushed `model_test_start` /
  `model_test_done` logs identify which model hangs or fails. Direct live checks
  through `/api/models/test` timed out after 20s for
  `nvidia/z-ai/glm-5.1` and `nvidia/minimaxai/minimax-m2.7`, and the
  post-deploy corrected sweep reproduced the same 20s timeout for both models.
  The corrected sweep also passed `codestral/codestral-latest`, so the command
  path is valid. OmniRoute's provider connection test still returns
  `valid:true` for bogus model payloads, proving it is provider-key preflight
  only. OpenSpec TODO now tracks Nvidia model-test timeout investigation through
  OmniRoute logs or `/api/models/test-all` batches. Verification: provider
  sweep and CLI tests; ruff on touched files; `git diff --check`; and OpenSpec
  strict validation.
- Deploy fix: apply smoke now sends `stream=true` and treats non-empty SSE/text
  responses from the shared OmniRoute client as a smoke pass. Live real `apply`
  showed `fmo-grid-aux-text` returns HTTP 400 without streaming but succeeds
  with streaming, and combo smoke responses may be text/event-stream rather than
  JSON `choices`. Verification: focused apply/bootstrap tests, ruff on touched
  files, `git diff --check`, and OpenSpec strict validation.
- Deploy fix: apply now treats an empty desired target list as a degraded
  no-target skip, not as an instruction to delete every combo member. Live real
  `apply` hit this when `fmo-grid-aux-struct` had a degraded/no-primary plan and
  an existing seed combo; applying `[]` made smoke fail and rolled back. Empty
  target diffs are now reported as `skipped_empty_combos` with no PUT or smoke.
  Verification: focused apply/bootstrap tests, ruff on touched files, and
  OpenSpec strict validation.
- Deploy fix: apply now writes live combos through the UUID returned by
  `GET /api/combos` while still using the managed `name` for diff/drift/smoke
  identity. Live real `apply` proved the bridge returns UUID `id` plus
  `name=fmo-*`, but `PUT /api/combos/{name}` returns 404 whereas
  `PUT /api/combos/{uuid}` succeeds. Verification: focused apply/bootstrap
  tests, ruff on touched files, and OpenSpec strict validation.
- Deploy fix: request-window hard-stop apply safety now survives the
  `quota-sync` liveness overlay. Live `full --dry-run` refreshed Nvidia evidence
  to `remaining_source=live_observed`, `percent_remaining=0`, and
  `locked_out=true` from a future reset, even though the researched RPM
  hard-stop rule still had request capacity above the safety buffer. The apply
  gate now treats minute/hour request-window rules as request capacity and does
  not require daily/monthly liveness to pass for that case. Verification:
  focused apply/bootstrap tests, ruff on touched files, and OpenSpec strict
  validation.
- Deploy fix: apply now evaluates only the newest diff snapshot per role, so
  stale legacy `fmo-fmo-*` diff rows from the earlier combo-id bug no longer
  appear as unmanaged combos during `full --dry-run`. The bootstrap precondition
  path reuses the same latest-diff selector. Code Simplifier review kept the
  selector as one small apply-stage helper shared by bootstrap. Verification:
  focused apply/bootstrap tests, ruff on touched files, and OpenSpec strict
  validation.
- Deploy fix: provider endpoints now use provider/model/type identity, not
  provider-account/model/type identity, so catalog updates overwrite a single
  endpoint row even when OmniRoute exposes several account/pool rows for the
  same provider. The v3.23 migration backfills `provider_id`, moves dependent
  rows from duplicates to a keeper endpoint, deletes duplicate endpoints, and
  adds the provider-level unique constraint. Code Simplifier review kept the
  repository upsert as the single production writer. Verification: focused
  persistence/foundation/catalog/bootstrap/apply tests and ruff on touched
  files.
- Deploy fix: the service entrypoint now derives apply preconditions from the
  latest diff snapshots with the same quota/probe safety as the apply stage.
  Live `apply --dry-run` had passed the stage-local Nvidia request-window quota
  check, but the older bootstrap guard still rejected apply by checking all
  historical probes and stale allocation-plan flags. Code Simplifier review kept
  bootstrap as a thin caller of the apply-stage safety logic. Verification:
  focused bootstrap/apply tests, ruff on touched files, `git diff --check`, and
  OpenSpec strict validation.
- Deploy fix: model matching now prefers existing canonical AA slugs before the
  provider-catalog fallback and carries the matched canonical slug into the
  endpoint binding. Provider punctuation/tuning aliases such as
  `minimax-m2.7` -> `minimax-m2-7` and `gemma-3n-e2b-it` -> `gemma-3n-e2b` are
  accepted as exact-slug matches. Live evidence showed AA did contain both
  canonical families, but model matching had created separate provider slugs,
  leaving passed Nvidia seeds without scorer metrics. Follow-up fix makes
  AA-backed canonical slugs win alias collisions against stale provider-specific
  canonical rows left by previous matching and removes unreferenced stale aliases
  during rematch so updates overwrite canonical binding instead of accumulating
  duplicates.
- Deploy fix: `sync-metadata` now routes through the composed production
  external-metadata stage instead of returning a no-op success when a runtime
  pipeline runner is present. The metadata repository also persists Artificial
  Analysis snapshot rows into `artificial_analysis_model_metrics`, so role
  scoring can read canonical AA metrics instead of only provider-quality
  observations. This addresses live `quality_gate:unverifiable` rows caused by
  an empty scorer metrics table after a successful-looking metadata command.
  Follow-up fix switches production metadata sync to the AA free-tier endpoint
  required by the live spec; live pro endpoint returned `http_error` after the
  key was installed.
  Code Simplifier review kept the CLI dispatch and persistence changes explicit.
  Verification: focused metadata/CLI/runtime tests, ruff on touched files,
  `git diff --check`, and OpenSpec strict validation.
- Deploy fix: context eligibility now treats `minimum_context_window = 0` as no
  hard context requirement, so live seed endpoints with unknown context are not
  rejected from no-minimum roles. Unknown context still fails closed for roles
  with a real positive minimum unless manual override is set. Follow-up fix
  bumps the immutable role score version to `production-v2-context`, because
  live `production-v1` rows reused the old context rejection when input hashes
  did not change. Code Simplifier review kept the fix to explicit versioning
  plus a scorer anchor. Verification: focused scoring/runtime tests, ruff on
  touched files, `git diff --check`, and OpenSpec strict validation.
- Deploy fix: quota research now retries `/v1/search` without a pinned provider
  when `gemini-grounded-search` returns 429, and falls back from `answer.text` to
  result titles/snippets. This matches live OmniRoute: default search succeeds
  through `exa-search` while `gemini-grounded-search` is rate-limited. Probe
  requests now set `stream=true`, fixing Nvidia-style providers that reject
  OmniRoute-injected `stream_options` unless streaming is enabled. Code
  Simplifier review added the probe stream anchor and split fallback test
  responsibilities. Follow-up fix narrows provider-wide probing to current
  one-member combo seeds when wildcard quota rules confirm many endpoints, so
  live Nvidia probing no longer blasts unavailable catalog entries before
  scoring can start. Streaming probe evidence uses a new suite version/hash, so
  old same-day failed probe rows no longer block apply after a fixed probe pass.
- Deploy fix: quota research now treats provider/account search as a topology
  discovery step before quota activation. Provider-wide or RPM-only answers can
  still write wildcard rules, but model-group/per-model answers fail closed
  instead of being widened to `model_pattern='*'`. Requests-per-minute/hour are
  now usable request capacity and normalize to conservative daily request
  ceilings, matching providers such as Nvidia that publish RPM without daily or
  monthly token caps. Code Simplifier review added an anchor at the topology
  guard and kept group-pattern extraction deferred in OpenSpec TODO.
- Deploy fix: provider/account quota research filters now cast optional CLI
  filters to text before `IS NULL` checks, matching live Postgres parameter
  typing. Live `research-quotas --provider antigravity` previously failed before
  running search with `could not determine data type of parameter`. Code
  Simplifier review kept the fix to SQL typing only. Verification: ruff on the
  quota stage, `git diff --check`, and OpenSpec strict validation.
- Deploy fix: quota research now defaults to provider/account pool scope instead
  of per-model scanning. A triggered recalc searches each provider/account once,
  persists wildcard rules with `model_pattern='*'`, and access classification
  applies exact model rules first, then provider/account wildcard rules. The
  explicit `--endpoint` path remains only for diagnostics and writes an exact
  model rule. Code Simplifier review replaced repeated `DISTINCT ON` expressions
  with explicit grouping keys and `row_number()`. Focused verification:
  provider-pool/access/quota-filter tests invoked on Python 3.12 venv (skipped
  locally due PostgreSQL `/dev/shm` exhaustion), ruff on touched files, and
  OpenSpec strict validation.
- Deploy fix: provider probes now use the shared `/v1/chat/completions` route
  with a tiny completion budget and no-cache header, and the shared OmniRoute
  client returns text/SSE bodies as probe content when a successful response is
  not JSON. Probe content that is actually a free-resource denial now fails
  closed even with HTTP 200. Quota research also honors `--endpoint` so live
  seed endpoints can be researched one at a time instead of scanning all 698
  free models. Code Simplifier review kept the client fallback, probe route, and
  endpoint filter as separate simple changes. Focused verification:
  probe/client/quota-filter tests on Python 3.12 venv (DB-backed filter test
  skipped locally due PostgreSQL `/dev/shm` exhaustion), ruff on touched files,
  and OpenSpec strict validation.
- Deploy fix: probing now persists shared-client HTTP errors as failed endpoint
  probes instead of crashing the stage. Live `probe-models` hit HTTP 400 from a
  provider completion route; the stage now records status/reason details, marks
  that endpoint `probe_status=failed`, and keeps the batch moving. Code
  Simplifier review extracted suite selection once for normal/error paths.
  Focused verification: probe/scoring tests on Python 3.12 venv (DB-backed
  probe-stage tests skipped locally due PostgreSQL `/dev/shm` exhaustion), ruff
  on touched files, and OpenSpec strict validation.
- Deploy fix: shared OmniRoute client `post`/`put` now preserve call-site
  headers while still adding management auth, `Idempotency-Key`, and
  `X-Request-Id`. Live probing needed this for `X-OmniRoute-No-Cache`; before
  the fix `probe-models` crashed with an unexpected `headers` keyword before any
  provider probe could run. Code Simplifier review kept the change at the client
  boundary. Focused verification: foundation/probe/e2e tests, ruff on touched
  files, and OpenSpec strict validation.
- Deploy fix: access classification now treats missing quota research as
  endpoint-local fail-closed state (`unknown` / `quota_rule_missing`) instead of
  aborting the whole batch. This lets live endpoints with active quota rules
  continue into probe/score/allocation while silent models stay unusable until a
  numeric quota source or calibration exists. Code Simplifier review kept the
  fix scoped to the access stage plus live spec/TODO docs. Focused verification:
  ruff on touched files, OpenSpec strict validation, and focused pytest invoked
  on the project Python 3.12 venv (skipped locally because PostgreSQL initdb
  cannot allocate `/dev/shm`).
- Deploy fix: production Postgres and the baseline schema now allow
  `role_consumers.consumer_type='auxiliary'`, matching Hermes inventory output
  for auxiliary model slots. The live shlinker FMO dry-run no longer fails on
  Hermes auxiliary slots after the constraint migration. Code Simplifier review
  kept the change to schema/migration docs only.
- Deploy fix: Hermes inventory now treats a present but empty Hermes
  `state.db` with no `sessions` table as no observed demand instead of
  crashing. This matches the live shlinker Hermes state shape and keeps
  `sync-hermes-inventory` on bootstrap defaults until runtime sessions appear.
  Code Simplifier review kept the fix scoped to the `sessions` table probe.
  Focused verification: `tests/test_hermes_inventory_real_shapes.py`,
  `tests/test_spec_coverage.py`, and `git diff --check`.
- `update-aa-index-migration-inspector` is archived: the migration agent
  now uses `reference/prompts/aa-index-migration.md` through
  `LlmSiteConfig.prompt_path`, receives deterministic old/new index context,
  role/capacity/distribution/percentile facts, and no longer gets selected-model
  JSON as its prompt. `aa-index analyze` lets the shared runtime resolver own
  model selection, proposals use typed `threshold_value` fields, validation
  emits explicit operational error codes, invalid advice enters a bounded repair
  loop, and rollout revalidates current repository state before inserting
  threshold versions. Focused verification: AA migration/advisory/runtime/spec
  coverage tests, ruff, and OpenSpec strict for the change. Code Simplifier
  prep added explicit validator/context/rollout anchors and kept the
  machine-used proposal schema to `threshold_value`. Archive merged
  aa-index-migration and llm-runtime deltas into living specs.
- `update-smart-combo-review-context` is archived: the diff stage now
  builds a deterministic reviewer context containing role id, current combo,
  target combo, minimal diff, role requirements, demand forecast, allocation
  constraints, bounded candidate registry, quota summary, diversity summary,
  validation report, and apply-precondition summary. `run_combo_review` renders
  `reference/prompts/smart-combo-reviewer.md` through `LlmSiteConfig.prompt_path`,
  redacts secret-like values, and keeps `ComboReviewResponse`/persisted advisory
  payload stable. Focused verification: advisory/runtime/diff/e2e/spec coverage
  tests, ruff, and OpenSpec strict for the change. Archive merged the
  smart-combo-reviewer delta into the living spec.
- `update-combo-member-identity` is archived: allocation targets now
  include endpoint id, structured OmniRoute `combo_step`, provider account, quota
  pool, canonical model, canonical slug/family, and score metadata. Combo
  construction avoids duplicate canonical models when a safe alternative exists,
  reports canonical-family concentration, and keeps quota-pool capacity as the
  hard gate. Diff/apply snapshots now store structured members plus endpoint-id
  audit fields, and apply sends structured model steps while keeping drift,
  idempotency, smoke, rollback, and dry-run behavior. Focused verification:
  allocation/apply/profile/advisory/spec coverage tests, ruff, and OpenSpec
  strict for the change. Archive merged allocator, combo-applier, and
  audit-rollback deltas into living specs.
- `update-quota-research-range-resolution` is ready to archive: quota research
  now renders the quota inspector prompt from `reference/prompts/quota-research.md`,
  threads `previous_limit` into that prompt, exposes deterministic range-clamp
  policy tests, and expands the search query to ask for cumulative request/token
  budget axes plus hard-stop evidence from official and community sources.
  Shared Inspector resolution is complete: quota, Hermes forecast, and Hermes
  intelligence Inspectors leave `LlmSiteConfig.model` unset, render configured
  prompt files, require a resolver-selected concrete provider model, and fail
  closed as `llm_model_unavailable` without one. Code Simplifier review kept the
  deterministic fallback and safe-mode activation unchanged while removing the
  fabricated Inspector combo fallback from code and specs.
- `update-quota-research-range-resolution` archived on 2026-06-23 via
  `npx --yes @fission-ai/openspec@latest archive ... --skip-specs --yes` after
  manually confirming/merging living spec deltas. Post-archive checks passed:
  full pytest, OpenSpec `--all --strict`, spec coverage/doc gates, and
  `git diff --check`. The OpenSpec CLI invocation is now documented as the
  always-used npx form.
- `add-intelligence-inspector` is ready to archive: Hermes inventory now carries
  profile/cron/auxiliary describing text, runs the advisory intelligence
  Inspector per describing unit, caches verdicts by content hash, maps tier/axis
  to role quality anchors, persists anchor metadata for role scoring, and exposes
  deterministic grid profile/snap/bootstrap helpers. Code Simplifier review
  tightened the cache-hit test setup and added an anchor on the content-hash
  refresh boundary. Static gates also surfaced a stale quota-summary
  `previous_limit` signature and a missing `timedelta` test import; the minimal
  fixes restored safe-mode derivation and static lint.
- `refactor-unify-shared-helpers` is archived: row helpers remain single-home in
  `persistence/_base.py`, timestamp/slug/hash/idempotency-key helpers now live
  in `idempotency.py`, quota payload math lives in `quota_normalize.py`, and the
  stage shims import those canonical helpers. Code Simplifier review preserved
  exact combo-state hash behavior while removing duplicate local definitions.
- `refactor-extract-test-fakes` is archived: the shared composition fake
  clients/runtimes now live in `tests/_clients.py`, common test helpers live in
  `tests/_composition_support.py`, composition tests are split by stage domain,
  and `tests` is importable under both pytest entry points. Code Simplifier
  review kept the generated split as explicit imports plus a support-module
  `__all__` instead of star imports.
- `refactor-split-stages-apply` is archived: demand forecast, allocation,
  diff/apply, rollback, audit, and cross-cluster helper wrappers now resolve
  through dedicated `composition_stages` modules behind the package shim. Code
  Simplifier review kept this slice behavior-preserving and left deeper helper
  deduplication to the existing `refactor-unify-shared-helpers` slice.
- `refactor-split-stages-runtime` is archived: probing, telemetry, Hermes
  inventory, role lifecycle, role scoring, and the role-scoring helper cluster
  now resolve through dedicated `composition_stages` modules behind the package
  shim. Code Simplifier review kept wrappers behavior-preserving and left shared
  helper extraction for the apply/helper slice.
- `refactor-split-stages-discovery` is archived: `fmo.composition_stages` now
  starts as a package, with discovery/quota/access cluster modules and a shim
  preserving existing composition imports and production adapter wiring. Code
  Simplifier review kept the package-shim anchor and focused the wrappers on the
  moved front-stage boundary.
- `refactor-split-persistence` is archived: `fmo.persistence` is now a package
  with `_base.py` plus one repository module per aggregate, `__init__.py`
  re-exports the previous public API, and static pyright issues that surfaced
  after enabling the gate were narrowed/fixed. Code Simplifier review added the
  import-stability anchor on the package shim before commit.
- `prefer-learned-quota-with-liveness` is archived: live OmniRoute learned
  `quotaTotal`/`quotaUsed` now remain a reactive request-rate signal, live
  liveness (`percentRemaining`, lockout, null healthy `resetAt`) is persisted
  separately from research/calibration daily budget capacity, and apply gates on
  confirmed-free + hard-stop + fresh probe + known daily budget + healthy
  liveness. Code Simplifier review added anchors at the daily-budget/live-rate
  boundary so future changes do not remerge those units.
- `add-rollback-idempotency` is archived: in-apply smoke-failure reverts and
  top-level rollback restores now pass an idempotency key derived from the
  restored combo state; the executable pending coverage allowlist is empty.
- `harden-pipeline-resilience` is archived: pipeline partial/stale results now
  continue through later stages while preserving exit 2, quota research degrades
  per endpoint, and apply rejects stale, assumed, or zero-buffer quota evidence.
  Code Simplifier review wired the configured apply safety-buffer value through
  the apply gate instead of leaving the config field unused.
- `fix-selection-correctness` is archived: production role scoring now derives
  benchmark, latency, health, stability, quota headroom, and uncertainty from
  persisted AA/telemetry/quota evidence; allocation consumes shared pool
  capacity and reserves every scored combo member. Code Simplifier review pulled
  repeated AA score config out of the scoring loop and tightened combo
  reservation branching before commit.
- Auto-router fallback tail now has a structured ordered config, exact
  membership matching, AA/quality-gate exemptions, and allocation appends
  eligible routers after scored endpoints without consuming scored slots.
- Weekly tokens-per-request recalibration now has a transaction-scoped job that
  refines the global factor from calibration observations, recomputes only
  self-derived capacities, and is fired by its own scheduler cron under the
  daily run lock.
- Quota manager now assembles research, calibrated and live quota axes into
  request-equivalent daily binding capacity, converts live quota token totals
  and usage, and keeps effective remaining in the same normalized unit.
- Quota research now captures request and token axes from deterministic summaries,
  preserves both axes on active rules, routes sub-day request rates out as
  reactive gates, and applies the same routing to Instructor inspector claims.
- Quota unit normalization now has explicit OpenSpec deltas for quota-manager
  and telemetry-sync, binds conversion/config/token telemetry scenarios to
  executable tests, captures OmniRoute analytics token counts without fabricating
  missing values, and records future active-slice coverage in
  `tests/spec_coverage_pending.txt` plus `openspec/TODO.md`.
- Active implementation slices are archived: production pipeline composition,
  metadata persistence, apply-precondition derivation, and scheduler service
  entrypoint.
- Production CLI dispatch now composes repository-backed pipeline stages and
  diagnostics from validated startup config.
- Metadata sync output is persisted through the repository; dry-run validates
  without writes.
- Apply fails closed from repository guard state and exits 5 when DB/snapshot,
  desired state, quota safety, or probe/smoke evidence is missing or failing.
- `serve` owns the scheduler cron path and routes scheduled/manual/event/urgent
  triggers through persistent run locks.
- Scanner and free-registry persistence now write provider/account/catalog,
  endpoint, registry snapshot, and free-model rows through repository methods;
  source regression tests reject embedded table SQL in those stage modules.
- Production composition now dispatches `sync-free-registry` and
  `scan-providers` through registry/scanner adapters, removes the shared
  `_domain_stage_adapter` no-op, and requires explicit per-stage adapters for
  canonical domain stages at the adapter-backed boundary.
- Unwired canonical stages now fail closed with `not_implemented` (exit 3), and
  the executable effect harness rejects `success` results that lack a declared
  repository write, OmniRoute call, or idempotent no-change effect.
- All active OpenSpec implementation slices in this batch are archived; the
  executable scenario pending allowlist is empty.
- Production composition now wires `model-matching`, `quota-research`, and
  `access-classification` to their domain modules. Matching writes canonical
  endpoint bindings, quota research writes content-hashed summary snapshots and
  capped rules, and access classification writes canonical attribution status
  plus evidence. Missing quota payloads fail closed.
- Production composition now wires `probing`, `telemetry-sync`, and
  `quota-sync`. Probing is gated on confirmed access with remaining capacity and
  persists probe rows, telemetry sync writes normalized health observations, and
  quota sync writes live quota observations plus remaining-quota state.
- Production composition now wires `role-scoring`, `allocation`, and `diff`.
  Scoring persists per-role endpoint scores, allocation persists one planned
  combo target set per role with constraint reports, and diff persists minimal
  combo changes without mutating OmniRoute.
- Production composition now wires `apply` and `audit` end to end. Apply checks
  repository-backed preconditions, mutates only `fmo-` combos, runs the real
  smoke path without `/api/combos/test`, rolls back on smoke failure, and
  reports the real combo-test signal. Audit persists apply records and drift
  detection.
- Production composition now builds the shared Instructor runtime from
  OmniRoute `/v1` config and API key, selects only confirmed-free LLM models by
  AA `intelligence_index` with bootstrap/no-LLM fallback, routes quota research
  through the inspector with deterministic fallback, and records smart-combo
  advisory output without mutating deterministic diffs.
- Production composition now includes a `hermes-inventory` stage before
  `role-scoring`, uses the selected Hermes source adapter, persists inventory
  runs and role consumers, bootstraps new roles, runs the Inspector prompt-only,
  and lets allocation consume Hermes-derived `calls_per_run` demand.
- `aa-index` CLI commands now dispatch through the runtime handler. Analyze and
  proposal steps run `run_migration_agent` through the shared runtime, persist
  advisory threshold proposals, and deterministic approve/rollout/rollback
  paths own threshold activation and rollback.
- Production composition now runs role lifecycle reconciliation and demand
  forecasting before allocation. Allocation consumes persisted forecast demand,
  cold-start roles get a non-zero floor, and historical reserve is applied once
  before later forecasts use the base demand.
- Run-lock acquisition is now database-atomic through a partial unique index on
  active held lock rows; repository tests cover two independent connections,
  fresh schema installs, and migration installs.
- Code Simplifier review cleaned the new scheduler tests by sharing the partial
  index assertion and making concurrent-thread completion explicit.
- Apply stage now derives quota and probe safety from persisted endpoint state
  for desired `fmo-` combos. Missing, stale, non-hard-stop, or exhausted quota
  evidence and missing/stale/failing probes return `unsafe_to_apply` before any
  OmniRoute combo mutation.
- Code Simplifier review changed apply-stage safety queries to compare endpoint
  ids as text so malformed desired ids fail closed as missing evidence instead
  of raising a UUID cast error.
- Runtime documentation checks now allow only the explicitly named active-slice
  scenario pending list, and require those remaining slices to be visible in
  `openspec/TODO.md`.
- Hermes inventory now reads profile main model slots and raw auxiliary blocks
  from each profile's `config.yaml`, ignoring stale list-summary model values;
  Code Simplifier added an anchor on that source-of-truth boundary.
- Apply now rebalances only live `fmo-` combos from the OmniRoute combo set,
  skips absent desired combos as `unmanaged_combo`, and removes the unwired
  unknown-role immediate inventory trigger.
- Hermes inventory now emits non-auto profile and gateway auxiliary model slots
  as `auxiliary` consumers, and shared-combo demand sums those slot consumers.
- Quality gates now persist upper bounds, derive seed-anchored bands from live
  combo seeds, widen bands to forecast demand, and order combo members weakest
  eligible first.
- Profile normalization now rewrites raw or missing Hermes model slots to live
  `fmo-` combos by canonical model, falls back to the default profile combo,
  supports dry-run reporting, backs up configs before atomic writes, and is
  exposed through `normalize-profiles`; focused review fixed nested gateway
  auxiliary slot writes before commit.
- Quota research now runs only on reachable free-model changes, skips unchanged
  free-registry snapshots without `/v1/search`, uses OmniRoute `quotaTotal` as
  a limit hint during triggered full recalc, and deactivates lost-free models so
  rebalance drops them while provider-model rows remain additive. Focused review
  added the probe/quota safety stages to rebalance tests before apply.
- New confirmed-free provider models are now additively registered in OmniRoute
  through `POST /api/provider-models` only when their provider has an existing
  connection and no endpoint already exists; paid, unreachable, and already-known
  models are skipped, and an integration test covers registered models flowing
  through scan, matching, quota, probe, scoring, and combo rebalance.
- Multi-combo apply now persists each successful `applied` snapshot before
  moving to the next combo, restores the failed combo plus all earlier applied
  combos on later smoke failure, cleans rolled-back applied snapshots, and
  still attempts every restore before returning `rollback_failed`.
- Apply now compares the live combo baseline captured at apply time with the
  diff-time `before` state before mutating. Divergence returns
  `unsafe_to_apply` without overwriting manual/live changes, and rollback uses
  the live pre-mutation baseline.
- Top-level `rollback` now runs a dedicated combo revert path for `--run-id`,
  `--role`, or `--endpoint`, restores persisted `applied` snapshots to their
  pre-change combo state, records `rollback_reverted` audit entries, returns
  exit 7 on restore failure, and leaves `aa-index rollback` as the only AA
  threshold rollback path.
- Composition is now split into a thin root plus `composition_stages`,
  `aa_index_runtime`, and `composition_contracts`, with a structural test
  guarding the module boundary and the full suite passing without DB skips.
- Apply smoke now evaluates real OpenAI-compatible chat completion bodies:
  non-empty `choices[0].message.content` passes, empty content fails, and
  `OmniRouteRequestError` maps to rollback instead of a crash. Fabricated
  top-level `status_code` smoke fixtures are removed from production apply tests.
- CLI dry-run now executes selected pipeline stages instead of returning
  unconditional success. `apply --dry-run` runs guard/drift validation, reports
  unsafe gates, and skips combo mutation, smoke calls, and `/api/combos/test`.
- OmniRoute GET calls now retry bounded transient `502/503/504` and transport
  failures with per-attempt request ids. POST remains non-retriable and carries
  caller-supplied `Idempotency-Key`; apply combo writes pass their idempotency
  hash through that header.
- Production role scoring now applies context-window and quality-gate hard
  filters before weighted scoring, persists context/quality rejection reasons,
  surfaces endpoint rejection diagnostics, and skips new allocation plans while
  a role quality gate needs AA index recalibration.
- The canonical pipeline now includes a real `account-discovery` stage after
  candidate discovery and before quota/scoring inputs. `discover-accounts`
  dispatches to that stage, quota-pool membership and independence status are
  persisted, rate-limit failures stay conservative, and allocation uses
  account quota pools instead of double-counting same-pool accounts.
- Recorded slink fixtures now cover live OmniRoute combo rows and Hermes empty
  live state; formerly stub-heavy registration, composition, and role-lifecycle
  tests now replay recorded OmniRoute/Hermes bodies as their base inputs, with
  only scenario-specific overlays kept local to the test. Code Simplifier review
  cleaned the prompt assertion formatting before commit.
- OmniRoute combo management bridge routes are exposed in the fork and deployed:
  `GET /api/combos` and `GET|PUT /api/combos/fmo-*` are allowlisted on the API
  bridge (OmniRoute commit `886ceb750`); `POST /api/combos/test` intentionally
  stays bridge `404` (apply uses the real `/v1` smoke path). Production
  `/opt/apps/omniroute` is pinned to `origin/main` (`a5a77e484`) and verified live
  on `127.0.0.1:20129` (`GET /api/combos` → `401`, not a bridge `404`). Prod
  `apply`/`diff`/`full` can now reach combo management. Tracked in
  `openspec/TODO.md`.
- No-auth quota calibration now resolves `opencode -> opencode-zen` as shared
  quota/model capacity, keeps alias misses and unknown no-auth providers
  inactive, and promotes only complete operator-observed OmniRoute token usage
  evidence.
- Hermes inventory trigger coverage now binds daily full inventory, explicit
  manual full inventory, and the unknown-role no-inventory/no-combo guard to
  executable scheduler tests; the matching pending allowlist entries are removed.
- Executable-spec pending coverage is empty again after binding the no-auth
  quota calibration scenarios.
- Fingerprint-backed provider connections now expand into deterministic
  per-fingerprint account scopes, persist stable account refs, parent metadata
  and `account-fingerprint` pool membership, fan scanner endpoints out to those
  virtual accounts, and remove the matching `account-discovery::*` pending
  coverage entries. Targeted tests cover fixture-backed pool multiplication,
  duplicate dedupe, missing-fingerprint shared fallback, scanner fanout,
  persistence, allocation, and the spec coverage gate.
- models.dev catalog fetch now retries transient transport failures and
  `502/503/504/429` responses with bounded injectable backoff, honors bounded
  `Retry-After`, preserves first-response failures for non-transient status and
  invalid JSON, and removes the retry scenarios from spec coverage pending.
- Final full-suite audit fixed quota-research all-failed status mapping and
  tightened rebalance fixtures so apply safety sees live quota evidence on the
  exact provider account selected by catalog scan.
- Stage-body drain now removes the `composition_stages/_legacy.py` monolith,
  keeps stage definitions in domain modules, and removes the helper alias layer;
  final spec-coverage audit bound the newly archived architecture scenarios to
  the structural runtime-doc tests.
- Live matcher cleanup now loads the previous endpoint canonical binding before
  rematch, so AA-backed canonical aliases overwrite stale provider-specific
  aliases and stale canonical rows are deleted instead of duplicated, including
  orphan alias rows left by earlier rematches.
- Live quality-band seeding now counts capacity only from probe-passed
  confirmed-free endpoints, so failed Nvidia candidates cannot narrow a seed
  band and exclude the actually routable free models.
- Allocation now filters scored endpoints per role before combo construction
  and deduplicates endpoint ids inside each priority combo, preventing a single
  live endpoint from being emitted twice for one combo.
- Global allocation now respects role-scoped score rows before reserving a
  primary, so an endpoint eligible for one role cannot make an unrelated role
  appear planned with an empty combo.
- Combo diff snapshot re-runs now refresh the existing content-identical row's
  recency and run id instead of leaving an older empty diff hidden behind a newer
  superseded diff.
- Apply quota safety now accepts researched hard-stop request-window providers
  such as Nvidia RPM-only free tiers when request remaining is above the safety
  buffer, treating future reset timestamps as the next rate-window reset rather
  than lockout while plain assumed quota without such a rule still fails closed.
